The Chronicle Nqobile Tshili, Chronicle Reporter AN inferno on Friday morning razed down a hostel at Hillside Teachers College in Bulawayo destroying property worth millions of dollars. <img class="alignnone wp-image-468338 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/09/Hillsidee.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/09/Hillsidee.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/09/Hillsidee-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The fire is suspected to have been caused by an electric fault. Bulawayo Fire brigade teams attended the incident, but not before the hostel’s entire second floor was consumed by the fire. More details to follow…